SHELL PROGRAMMING

The shell scripts that make use of the following:

o Operators - &&, ||

o Test command

o Statements – break and continue

o Arrays

o Functions

o File creation and accessing for read and write

SPOT EXERCISE

Write shell scripts for the following problems:

1. a. Compare two strings S1 and S2. 

b. Compare two strings S1 and S2 using function.

(print 1 – when strings are same, 0 – when strings are different).

Do this for at least 2 pairs of strings.

2. Maintain an array for all week days 

a. Print only the week days – do not use any looping statement

b. Print every alternate day staring from Tuesday.
